data.024: Other Unlisted Reason - The reason for the application error condition cannot be described using any other code on the standard code list
data.027: Customer Identification Number Does not Exist
data.028: Customer Identification Number and Entity Name Do not Match
data.801: Missing or Invalid Transaction Handling Code
data.802: Invalid Debit or Credit Flag Code
data.803: Missing or Invalid Payment Method Code
data.806: Missing or Invalid Financial Institution Transit Routing Number
data.807: Missing or Invalid Originating Account Number
data.808: Missing or Invalid Receiving Account Number
data.811: Payment Received Too Far in Advance
data.812: Missing Transaction Reference or Trace Number
data.813: Missing or Invalid Payee Name and Address
data.814: Received After Cutoff Date or Time
data.825: Payment Amount Exceeds Approved Credit Limit; Refused
data.831: Missing or Invalid Cancellation Type Code
data.833: Invalid Cancellation Request (Item Not in Financial Warehouse to Cancel)
data.834: Missing or Invalid Effective Payment Date
data.A: Missing or Invalid Report Type Code
data.ASA: Associated Authorization - Other vehicles contained on a multilevel railcar have different shipper authorized destinations than this vehicle
data.ASV: Associated Vehicle Identification Number(s) Unknown - Other vehicles contained on a multilevel railcar are unknown to the shipper
data.AVE: Associated Vehicle Identification Number(s) Invalid - Vehicle Identification Numbers (DE539) for other vehicles contained on a multilevel railcar fail check digit verification
data.B: Missing or Invalid Physical Inventory Code
data.CAL: Currency Calculation - The amount calculated using the specified exchange rate exceeds the maximum length of the application data field
data.COV: Conflicting Authorizations - Commodities are moving on same Freight Bill which have conflicting contract rates or terms
data.CUR: Invalid Currency Code - Currency Code (DE100) reported is invalid
data.DBL: Duplicate Bill of Lading Number - Carrier has reused a shippers authorization number assigned to another shipment
data.DDT: Departure Date Invalid - The move/service date precedes the authorized date
data.DRC: Duplicate Railcar Departure - The railcar reported has a conflicting previous departure on the same date
data.DTE: Incorrect Date - The reported date is incorrect (e.g. premature date for transaction or non-existent date such as February 30)
data.DUP: Duplicate Transaction - The identical transaction has been transmitted more than once within the same input file
data.E: Missing or Invalid Material Condition Code
data.G: Missing or Invalid Processing (Count) Date Code
data.H: Missing or Invalid Unit of Measure Code
data.HUG: Quantity of Handling Units Shipped Greater Than the Quantity Specified
data.HUL: Quantity of Handling Units Shipped Less Than the Quantity Specified
data.I: Missing or Invalid Source of Supply Code
data.ICA: Invalid Claim Amount - Claim Total does not equal total of claim Line Item Totals
data.ICG: Invalid Charge Allowance Qualifier - The Charge Allowance Qualifier (DE538) reported is invalid
data.IDC: Invalid Decline/Amend Reason Code - The Decline/Amend Reason Code (DE548) reported is invalid
data.IMD: Invalid Railcar Type - The Equipment Description Code (DE40) reported is invalid
data.INC: Incomplete Transaction - Optional Element(s) required by the application are missing
data.INF: Invalid Status Code - The Vehicle Status Code (DE1094) reported is invalid
data.IPR: Status Code Previously Reported - The status code reported has previously been processed by the receiver
data.L: Missing or Invalid Support Request Code
data.LOC: Invalid Damage Area Code - The Damage Area Code (DE556) reported is invalid
data.M: Missing or Invalid Supply Condition Code
data.MB: Missing or Invalid Purchase Order Number
data.MBL: Multiple Bills of Lading - Multiple Bills of Lading have been transmitted for a 3 for 2 shipment (only one bill of lading is required)
data.MC: Missing or Invalid Bill of Lading Number
data.MF: Missing or Invalid Internal Vendor Number
data.MK: Missing or Invalid Ship Date Location
data.ML: Missing or Invalid Sell to Location
data.MM: Missing or Invalid Bill to Location
data.NAU: Not Authorized - The move/service reported by the carrier has not been authorized by the shipper
data.NCL: No Clearance Authorization - The vessel clearance reported by the carrier has not been authorized by the shipper
data.NCR: No Clearance Reported - The freight bill submitted by the carrier precedes the vessel clearance
data.NDP: No Departure Reported - The railcar arrival has been received prior to the railcar departure
data.NDT: No Termination Date - The move/service/status change reported requires termination of a previously transmitted Vehicle Status Code (DE1094)
data.NIF: Invalid Status Location - The location reported with the Status Code (DE1094) does not match any move/service locations authorized by the shipper
data.NOD: Not on Departure - Vehicle Identification Numbers reported on railcar arrival do not match Vehicle Identification Numbers reported on railcar departure
data.NRA: No Railcar Arrival - A subsequent shipper authorized move/service has been reported prior to reported arrival of a railcar
data.PND: Pending Payment - The freight bill/invoice/waybill has previously been transmitted and is awaiting maturity of credit terms prior to payment
data.PPD: Previously Paid - The freight bill/invoice/waybill has previously been paid
data.PRM: Primary Inspection Not Received - A Motor Vehicle Inspection Details transaction containing a Supplemental Inspection indicator (DE835) has been reported prior to the primary inspection
data.QTY: Quantity - The number of items on the freight bill/invoice/waybill does not equal the number of unique segments which specifically identify those items
data.RAT: No Rate Available - The shipper is unable to determine the rate for the move/service reported by the carrier
data.RTE: Invalid Shipper's Route Code - The shippers route code reported by the carrier is invalid
data.RU: Rate Unverifiable - Carrier is unable to verify the rate reported by the shipper
data.S: Missing or Unauthorized Transportation Mode/Method Code
data.SCA: Invalid SCAC - The Standard Carrier Alpha Code (DE140) reported is invalid
data.SCD: Invalid Vehicle Service Code - The Vehicle Service Code (DE1062) reported is invalid
data.SEV: Invalid Damage Severity Code - The Damage Severity Code (DE541) reported is invalid
data.SPL: Invalid SPLC Code - The Standard Point Location Code (DE154) is invalid
data.STA: Shipment Picked Up After the Date Specified by the Ship Window
data.STP: Shipment Picked Up Prior to the Date Specified by the Ship Window
data.STR: Invalid Storage Days Calculation - The number of storage days billed does not equal the difference between arrival date and departure date less grace days
data.TRN: Turnover - The vessel clearance reported was authorized by the consignee rather than by the shipper
data.TYP: Invalid Damage Type Code - The Damage Type Code (DE540) reported is invalid
data.U: Missing or Unauthorized Transaction Type Code
data.UAU: Used Authorization - The move/service reported has previously been reported as completed
data.UCN: Unknown Claim Number - The claim number reported by the carrier is unknown to the claimant
data.UKN: Unknown Move/Service - The move/service reported has not been mutually defined by the trading partners
data.UNV: Unknown Vehicle Identification Number - The reported Vehicle Identification Number (DE539) is unknown to the shipper
data.VIN: Invalid Vehicle Identification Number - The reported Vehicle Identification Number (DE53) fails the check digit calculation
data.VND: Vehicle Not Departed - Storage charges have been billed prior to reported departure of a vehicle from storage
data.VOS: Offsite Storage - Storage charges have been reported for an item known to be at another location
data.ZDS: Zero Storage Days - The arrival and departure dates are equal, per diem storage charges have not accrued
